FBIS4-13667 "drnes078_l_94004" FBIS-NES-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 ISRAEL Golan Lobby To Launch Information Campaign Golan Lobby To Launch Information Campaign TA2204052294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 22 Apr 94 TA2204052294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el English BFN [Excerpt] Activists working on behalf of keeping the Golan Heights under Israeli control say they are launching a giant campaign following Prime Minister Rabin's statement yesterday that he would be willing to dismantle settlements on the Golan Heights in exchange for peace with Syria. On the fallout from the preime minister's statement, David Ze'ev: [Begin Ze'ev recording] Golan Heights activists from around the country are said to be ready to launch what is being described as a giant demonstration and information campaign. Over 100 branches of the Golan movement are preparing for intensive activity during the coming weeks, following the prime minister's statement yesterday on dismantling Golan settlements. U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher has tried to lower expectations for his visit to the Middle East, which he announced will start Sunday, but Israel's Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin says the prime minister's statement yesterday was one of a series by Israeli officials recently that contribute to the possibility of changing the very slow pace of negotiations with Syria, as he put it, to something which is more intensive than that. [passage omitted] [end recording]
